SPECIFIC TERMS FOR BASA APPLICATION

This license applies to the BASA (Business Association of San Antonio) web application, including but not limited to:

PERMITTED USES:
✅ Educational purposes (learning, teaching, research)
✅ Personal projects and portfolios
✅ Non-profit organizations
✅ Community projects
✅ White labeling for non-commercial purposes
✅ Inspiration and reference for similar projects
✅ Academic research and publications

REQUIRED ATTRIBUTION:
When using this work, you must provide attribution to "Business Association of San Antonio (BASA)" in one of the following ways:
- Visible credit on the website/page
- Footer attribution
- About page or credits section
- Source code comments
- Documentation references

The attribution can be discreet but must be reasonably discoverable by users.

PROHIBITED USES:
❌ Commercial websites or applications
❌ For-profit businesses using the code for revenue generation
❌ SaaS platforms charging for access to features based on this code
❌ Reselling or redistributing for profit
❌ Using in commercial products or services

EXCEPTIONS:
- Non-profit organizations may use this code for their operations
- Educational institutions may use this code for teaching and research
- Personal projects that don't generate revenue are permitted

